      "title": "Adding and Subtracting",
      "topics": [],
      "fastest": false,
      "reverse": false,
      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "pos = input().split()\n\ntotal_x = 0\ntotal_y = 0\n\nfor i, e in enumerate(pos):\n    # Clean and split the coordinates\n    x, y = e.replace(\"(\", \"\").replace(\")\", \"\").split(\",\")\n    \n    # Always add x\n    total_x += int(x)\n    \n    # Logic for y:\n    if i == 0:\n        total_y = int(y)  # Set the starting number\n    else:\n        total_y -= int(y) # Subtract the rest\n\nprint(total_x, total_y)\n\n",
      "statement": "You must output the sum of all x positions. For the y positions, take the first y value and subtract all following y values from it.",
